<div>
	<p><strong>The Ministry’s political leadership consists of the minister, a state secretary and a political adviser. The most senior official in the Ministry is the secretary general, who assists and advises the minister and coordinates the work of the Ministry.</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The Ministry of Transport and Communications consists of&nbsp;six departments:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/en/dep/sd/about-the-ministry/organisation/departments/department-of-planning-administration-an.html?id=1572">Department of Strategy, Economic Affairs and Administration</a></li>
<li><a href="/en/dep/sd/about-the-ministry/organisation/departments/department-of-civil-aviation-postal-serv.html?id=332352">Department of Civil Aviation, Postal Services and Telecommunications</a></li>
<li><a href="/en/dep/sd/about-the-ministry/organisation/departments/department-for-public-roads-and-traffic-.html?id=635327">Department of Public Roads and Traffic Safety</a></li>
<li><a href="/en/dep/sd/about-the-ministry/organisation/departments/department-of-rail-transport.html?id=635328">Department of Public and Rail Transport</a></li>
<li><a href="/en/dep/sd/about-the-ministry/organisation/departments/department-of-coastal-management-and-mar.html?id=706783">Department of Coastal Management and Marine Environment</a></li>
<li><a href="/en/dep/sd/about-the-ministry/organisation/departments/communications-department.html?id=555839">Department of Press and Information</a></li>
</ul>
